# BinarySpell Static Site Generators

To add a static site generator of your choice do the following:

  1. Create a folder with the name of your static site generator e.g. hugo
  2. Create the following files in that directory
    1. README.md: explaining what the static site generator is
    2. Dockerfile: containing the code to build the image for this static site generator
    3. init.sh: script used to create the new repo, this gets the repo_name and repo_path as the args
    4. build.sh: script used to build the generator, this gets the repo_name, repo_path, and output_path as the args
